      <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>&lt;pre&gt;[Congressional Record Volume 169, Number 161 (Monday, October 2, 2023)][House]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [&lt;a href="https://www.gpo.gov"&gt;www.gpo.gov&lt;/a&gt;]By Mr. SELF:H.R. 5870.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article I, Section 8 of the United States Constitution,which states ``[t]he Congress shall have power to lay andcollect taxes, duties, imposts and excises, to pay the debtsand provide for the common defense and general welfare of theUnited States; but all duties, imposts and excises shall beuniform throughout the United States''The single subject of this legislation is:VA Board of Veterans' Appeals transparency regarding itsprocessing of appeals and the rights of veterans andsurvivors to pursue claims for VA benefits in a streamlinedmanner.[Page H4951]&lt;/pre&gt;</constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
    </cdata>
